          "text": "     1вҶ’---\n     2вҶ’name: make_task\n     3вҶ’description: Provides information necessary for creating a task or a set of tasks.\n     4вҶ’---\n     5вҶ’\n     6вҶ’> Important: be sure to use the `task_management` skill.\n     7вҶ’\n     8вҶ’## Task creation process\n     9вҶ’1. Receive request from user.\n    10вҶ’2. If user provided a research file, there's no need to call `research` independently.\n    11вҶ’3. Determine whether to describe everything in one task or split into a set of tasks\n    12вҶ’4. Create task identifier and task directory\n    13вҶ’5. Describe the task\n    14вҶ’6. Create a new subdirectory in the `.claude/tasks` directory (see section `How to determine which identifier to choose`)\n    15вҶ’7. Create a `task.md` file there, which will contain the full task description\n    16вҶ’\n    17вҶ’> Important: if you created multiple tasks - for each one start from item 4 and continue to the end.\n    18вҶ’\n    19вҶ’### How to determine how many tasks to create\n    20вҶ’1 task = minimum possible set of actions to achieve the desired goal.\n    21вҶ’First example:\n    22вҶ’```\n    23вҶ’User request: Fix CertificateCheckerImpl - Implement real SSL validation instead of a stub\n    24вҶ’> One task will be created\n    25вҶ’```\n    26вҶ’Second example:\n    27вҶ’```\n    28вҶ’User request: I have a set of issues. Need to do:\n    29вҶ’1) Add logout - Complete session and token cleanup\n    30вҶ’2) Add analytics - Track authorization success\n    31вҶ’3) Add tests - Unit and integration tests for all layers\n    32вҶ’4) State refactoring - Replace var state with StateFlow\n    33вҶ’\n    34вҶ’> Accordingly, 4 tasks will be created.\n    35вҶ’```\n    36вҶ’Third example:\n    37вҶ’```\n    38вҶ’User request: Our project lacks certificate checks for webView, also I noticed tokens are not exchanged on 400 error.\n    39вҶ’Also it's strange that token expiration is not considered\n    40вҶ’\n    41вҶ’> 3 tasks will be created:\n    42вҶ’- Add WebView certificate verification\n    43вҶ’- Implement token exchange for server-side errors\n    44вҶ’- Add token lifetime handling\n    45вҶ’```\n    46вҶ’\n    47вҶ’### How to determine which identifier to choose\n    48вҶ’The user must always explicitly provide an identifier\n    49вҶ’Example:\n    50вҶ’```\n    51вҶ’1) Create task PMM-12346 [Large task description]\n    52вҶ’2) Create tasks based on research files(provided by user). Start with GAMES-001 and continue incrementally\n    53вҶ’```\n    54вҶ’If the user didn't provide a task ID - ask for it. Don't make it up yourself.\n    55вҶ’\n    56вҶ’## Task structure\n    57вҶ’1. Task identifier and title\n    58вҶ’2. Problem statement\n    59вҶ’3. Task description - what needs to be done\n    60вҶ’4. Constraints specification\n    61вҶ’5. Team specification - which subagents will be included in the work\n    62вҶ’6. Task status + time of its update (YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss) \n    63вҶ’\n    64вҶ’\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n",
