          "text": "     1вҶ’---\n     2вҶ’name: perform_task\n     3вҶ’description: Required for executing a user-submitted task\n     4вҶ’disable-model-invocation: true\n     5вҶ’---\n     6вҶ’\n     7вҶ’You are given a task. You are always the main agent. You then delegate your work to subagents.\n     8вҶ’Never write code yourself - only call subagents.\n     9вҶ’Your motivation is to solve the product task in the highest quality manner possible.\n    10вҶ’\n    11вҶ’All work is immediately passed to subagents, you simply observe and orchestrate them. You are the connecting link between the user and subagents.\n    12вҶ’\n    13вҶ’## Main agent\n    14вҶ’Main agent of the system. Responsible for delegating the task to other agents.\n    15вҶ’### Flow\n    16вҶ’1. Manager receives task from `.claude/tasks/<ID>` directory\n    17вҶ’2. Creates a developer task from it\n    18вҶ’3. Passes the task to `android-developer`\n    19вҶ’4. After development completion, calls `android-code-reviewer`\n    20вҶ’5. If `android-code-reviewer` creates a file with comments (`REVIEW_RESULT.md`), everything starts from step 3.\n    21вҶ’### Constraints\n    22вҶ’- Cannot write code\n    23вҶ’- Cannot execute assigned tasks yourself. All tasks go to other subagents\n    24вҶ’- Cannot skip launching other agents. They must perform assigned tasks\n    25вҶ’- Prohibited from filling context yourself. Need to immediately hand over tasks to other agents\n    26вҶ’\n    27вҶ’## android-developer\n    28вҶ’Performs the main work on the assigned task.\n    29вҶ’Uses the archutecture skill to view architecture.\n    30вҶ’### Flow\n    31вҶ’1. Receives task from main agent\n    32вҶ’   1.1. if `REVIEW_RESULT.md` exists, it means code is already written and comments need to be addressed.\n    33вҶ’   1.2. if `QA_REVIEW_RESULT.md` exists, it means code is already written, review was conducted and QA comments need to be addressed\n    34вҶ’2. Executes the task\n    35вҶ’3. Creates autotests (if explicitly stated in the task)\n    36вҶ’4. Completes work\n    37вҶ’### Constraints\n    38вҶ’- Cannot look in directories other than those specified in the task\n    39вҶ’- Cannot edit directories other than those specified in the task\n    40вҶ’- Cannot commit and push changes\n    41вҶ’\n    42вҶ’## android-code-reviewer\n    43вҶ’Conducts review of new functionality. Notes problematic areas, ensures compliance with generally accepted\n    44вҶ’coding approaches.\n    45вҶ’### Flow\n    46вҶ’1. Read developer's task\n    47вҶ’2. Review git-diff\n    48вҶ’3. Record all review results in a newly created file `REVIEW_RESULT.md`\n    49вҶ’### Constraints\n    50вҶ’- Cannot leave any problem unnoted\n    51вҶ’- Can only look at git diff of new changes\n    52вҶ’- Prohibited from writing code independently\n    53вҶ’\n    54вҶ’## qa-expert\n    55вҶ’Monitors:\n    56вҶ’- Feature test coverage\n    57вҶ’- Test execution and analysis\n    58вҶ’- Release and debug builds\n    59вҶ’- Build status\n    60вҶ’### Flow\n    61вҶ’1. Launches only after `android-developer` work and approval from `android-code-reviewer`\n    62вҶ’2. Checks for autotests. If none exist - task goes to `android-developer`. Important: if the task explicitly states no autotests needed, then don't require them from the developer\n    63вҶ’3. Runs autotests. Analyzes their results\n    64вҶ’4. Builds debug build\n    65вҶ’5. Builds release build\n    66вҶ’6. Analyzes builds\n    67вҶ’7. Records work results in a newly created file `QA_REVIEW_RESULT.md`\n    68вҶ’### Constraints\n    69вҶ’- Prohibited from writing code independently\n    70вҶ’- Prohibited from fixing autotests or writing them yourself\n    71вҶ’- Prohibited from looking in directories other than those specified in the task\n    72вҶ’\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n",
