          "type": "user",
          "text": "     1вҶ’# Task Performer Plugin\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’Structured development workflow plugin for Claude Code with automated code review and QA verification for mobile applications.\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’## Overview\n     6вҶ’\n     7вҶ’Task Performer is a Claude Code plugin that orchestrates a complete development workflow for Android projects. It provides specialized agents and skills to handle:\n     8вҶ’\n     9вҶ’- **Development** - Implementation of features following best practices\n    10вҶ’- **Code Review** - Comprehensive code analysis with actionable feedback\n    11вҶ’- **QA Verification** - Build, tests, coverage, security, and accessibility checks\n    12вҶ’\n    13вҶ’## Installation\n    14вҶ’\n    15вҶ’In Claude Code, register the marketplace first:\n    16вҶ’`/plugin marketplace add memksim/workflow-marketplace`\n    17вҶ’\n    18вҶ’Then install the plugin from this marketplace:\n    19вҶ’`/plugin install task-performer@workflow-plugins`\n    20вҶ’\n    21вҶ’### Directory Structure\n    22вҶ’\n    23вҶ’After installation, your project should have:\n    24вҶ’\n    25вҶ’```\n    26вҶ’your-project/\n    27вҶ’в””в”Җв”Җ .claude/\n    28вҶ’    в””в”Җв”Җ tasks/\n    29вҶ’        в””в”Җв”Җ <TASK-ID>/\n    30вҶ’            в”ңв”Җв”Җ task.md\n    31вҶ’            в”ңв”Җв”Җ dev_result.md\n    32вҶ’            в”ңв”Җв”Җ review_result.md\n    33вҶ’            в””в”Җв”Җ qa_review_result.md\n    34вҶ’```\n    35вҶ’\n    36вҶ’## Agents\n    37вҶ’\n    38вҶ’### senior-android-developer\n    39вҶ’\n    40вҶ’Senior Android developer agent for:\n    41вҶ’- Architecture decisions (MVI, MVVM, Clean Architecture)\n    42вҶ’- Kotlin/Java implementation\n    43вҶ’- Jetpack Compose UI development\n    44вҶ’- Performance optimization\n    45вҶ’- Testing strategies\n    46вҶ’\n    47вҶ’### android-code-reviewer\n    48вҶ’\n    49вҶ’Code review specialist that analyzes:\n    50вҶ’- Architecture compliance\n    51вҶ’- Code style and conventions\n    52вҶ’- Bug detection (NPE, memory leaks, race conditions)\n    53вҶ’- Security vulnerabilities\n    54вҶ’\n    55вҶ’### qa-expert\n    56вҶ’\n    57вҶ’Quality assurance agent that verifies:\n    58вҶ’- Build status (debug/release)\n    59вҶ’- Autotest execution and results\n    60вҶ’- Test coverage analysis\n    61вҶ’- Security audit (OWASP Mobile Top 10)\n    62вҶ’- Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1 AA)\n    63вҶ’\n    64вҶ’## Skills\n    65вҶ’\n    66вҶ’### /make_task\n    67вҶ’\n    68вҶ’Creates a new task with the specified ID.\n    69вҶ’\n    70вҶ’```\n    71вҶ’/make_task ABC-123\n    72вҶ’```\n    73вҶ’\n    74вҶ’Prompts for:\n    75вҶ’- Title\n    76вҶ’- Problem description\n    77вҶ’- Task description\n    78вҶ’- Constraints\n    79вҶ’- Team members\n    80вҶ’\n    81вҶ’Creates `.claude/tasks/ABC-123/task.md` with status `Ready for dev`.\n    82вҶ’\n    83вҶ’### /perform_task\n    84вҶ’\n    85вҶ’Executes the full workflow for a task.\n    86вҶ’\n    87вҶ’```\n    88вҶ’/perform_task ABC-123\n    89вҶ’```\n    90вҶ’\n    91вҶ’Runs the complete pipeline(Unless otherwise stated in the task description):\n    92вҶ’1. **Development** - `senior-android-developer` implements the feature\n    93вҶ’2. **Code Review** - `android-code-reviewer` analyzes the code\n    94вҶ’3. **QA Verification** - `qa-expert` checks build, tests, security, accessibility\n    95вҶ’\n    96вҶ’## Workflow\n    97вҶ’\n    98вҶ’### User workflow\n    99вҶ’1. `/make_task ABC-123`\n   100вҶ’2. `/perform_task ABC-123`\n   101вҶ’\n   102вҶ’### Agents workflow\n   103вҶ’```mermaid\n   104вҶ’flowchart TD\n   105вҶ’\n   106вҶ’A[Ready for Dev]\n   107вҶ’A --> B[Dev in Progress]\n   108вҶ’B --> C[Ready for Review]\n   109вҶ’C --> D[Review in Progress]\n   110вҶ’D --> E[Ready for QA Review]\n   111вҶ’E --> F[QA Review in Progress]\n   112вҶ’F --> G[Verified]\n   113вҶ’\n   114вҶ’%% Rework loops\n   115вҶ’C -- changes requested --> A\n   116вҶ’F -- bugs found --> A\n   117вҶ’```\n   118вҶ’\n   119вҶ’## Task Files\n   120вҶ’\n   121вҶ’Each task generates several files:\n   122вҶ’\n   123вҶ’| File | Purpose |\n   124вҶ’|------|---------|\n   125вҶ’| `task.md` | Task description and status |\n   126вҶ’| `dev_result.md` | Development results |\n   127вҶ’| `review_result.md` | Code review findings |\n   128вҶ’| `qa_review_result.md` | QA verification results |\n   129вҶ’\n   130вҶ’## Examples\n   131вҶ’\n   132вҶ’Example files are available in the `skills/*/examples/` directories.\n   133вҶ’\n   134вҶ’## License\n   135вҶ’\n   136вҶ’MIT License - see [LICENSE](LICENSE) for details.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n",
