          "text": "     1вҶ’---\n     2вҶ’name: task_management\n     3вҶ’description: Gets information on how to work with tasks in this project.\n     4вҶ’user-invokable: false\n     5вҶ’---\n     6вҶ’\n     7вҶ’## What is a task\n     8вҶ’Each task is a directory with a name equal to the unique task identifier.\n     9вҶ’**Examples:**\n    10вҶ’```\n    11вҶ’1) Identifier: MUSIC-009 -> Directory .claude/tasks/MUSIC-009/\n    12вҶ’2) Identifier: FEED-1000 -> Directory .claude/tasks/FEED-1000/\n    13вҶ’```\n    14вҶ’\n    15вҶ’As mentioned earlier, a task is a directory. It contains a set of .md files. Their set may vary.\n    16вҶ’**Example:**\n    17вҶ’- task.md - the only mandatory and guaranteed file in a task. Others are optional\n    18вҶ’- dev_result.md\n    19вҶ’- code_review_result.md\n    20вҶ’- qa_review_result.md\n    21вҶ’- manual_qa_result.md\n    22вҶ’- task_history.md - history of status changes (optional)\n    23вҶ’\n    24вҶ’## task.md\n    25вҶ’\n    26вҶ’Task files are **Markdown files** (`.md`) with **YAML frontmatter** at the top.\n    27вҶ’\n    28вҶ’The frontmatter (between `---` markers) contains metadata, followed by regular Markdown content:\n    29вҶ’\n    30вҶ’```markdown\n    31вҶ’---\n    32вҶ’id: \"TASK-001\"\n    33вҶ’title: \"Implement user profile screen\"\n    34вҶ’type: feature              # feature | bug | refactor | research | docs\n    35вҶ’priority: 2                # 1-4 (1 = Critical, 2 = High, 3 = Medium, 4 = Low)\n    36вҶ’assignee: senior-android-developer\n    37вҶ’depends_on: []             # List of task IDs that must complete first\n    38вҶ’blocks: []                 # List of task IDs waiting for this task\n    39вҶ’created_at: \"2026-03-05T10:00:00Z\"\n    40вҶ’updated_at: \"2026-03-05T12:30:00Z\"\n    41вҶ’status: \"Ready for dev\"\n    42вҶ’attempt: 0                 # Number of execution attempts\n    43вҶ’---\n    44вҶ’\n    45вҶ’# TASK-001: Implement user profile screen\n    46вҶ’\n    47вҶ’## Problem Statement\n    48вҶ’\n    49вҶ’What problem needs to be solved and why.\n    50вҶ’\n    51вҶ’## Task Description\n    52вҶ’\n    53вҶ’Detailed description of what needs to be done.\n    54вҶ’\n    55вҶ’## Context\n    56вҶ’\n    57вҶ’- Links to documentation\n    58вҶ’- Related files\n    59вҶ’- Design (Figma)\n    60вҶ’- Architecture decisions\n    61вҶ’\n    62вҶ’## Constraints\n    63вҶ’\n    64вҶ’- Do not touch X\n    65вҶ’- Use Y pattern\n    66вҶ’- Backward compatibility requirements\n    67вҶ’\n    68вҶ’## Acceptance Criteria\n    69вҶ’\n    70вҶ’- [ ] Criterion 1\n    71вҶ’- [ ] Criterion 2\n    72вҶ’- [ ] Criterion 3\n    73вҶ’\n    74вҶ’## Artifacts\n    75вҶ’\n    76вҶ’- Source code: src/features/profile/\n    77вҶ’- Tests: src/test/features/profile/\n    78вҶ’\n    79вҶ’## Team Specification\n    80вҶ’\n    81вҶ’| Role | Agent |\n    82вҶ’|------|-------|\n    83вҶ’| Developer | senior-android-developer |\n    84вҶ’| Reviewer | android-code-reviewer |\n    85вҶ’| QA | qa-expert |\n    86вҶ’\n    87вҶ’## Status: Ready for dev\n    88вҶ’## Updated: 2026-03-05 10:00:00\n    89вҶ’```\n    90вҶ’\n    91вҶ’### Field Definitions\n    92вҶ’\n    93вҶ’| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n    94вҶ’|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n    95вҶ’| id | string | Yes | Unique task identifier (e.g., CORE-001) |\n    96вҶ’| title | string | Yes | Short task title |\n    97вҶ’| type | enum | Yes | One of: feature, bug, refactor, research, docs |\n    98вҶ’| priority | number | Yes | 1-4 (1=Critical, 2=High, 3=Medium, 4=Low) |\n    99вҶ’| assignee | string | No | Agent assigned to the task |\n   100вҶ’| depends_on | array | No | List of task IDs that block this task |\n   101вҶ’| blocks | array | No | List of task IDs that this task blocks |\n   102вҶ’| created_at | datetime | Yes | ISO 8601 timestamp |\n   103вҶ’| updated_at | datetime | Yes | ISO 8601 timestamp |\n   104вҶ’| status | string | Yes | Current task status |\n   105вҶ’| attempt | number | No | Number of execution attempts (default: 0) |\n   106вҶ’\n   107вҶ’> Important: This file is always guaranteed to exist. If it's not there - require the user to create it.\n   108вҶ’\n   109вҶ’---\n   110вҶ’\n   111вҶ’## Task Status\n   112вҶ’\n   113вҶ’Task status shows progress of each performer:\n   114вҶ’\n   115вҶ’### Core Statuses\n   116вҶ’\n   117вҶ’| Status | Description |\n   118вҶ’|--------|-------------|\n   119вҶ’| `Ready for dev` | Task waiting for developer to pick it up |\n   120вҶ’| `Dev in progress` | Developer has picked up the task |\n   121вҶ’| `Ready for review` | Developer completed work, waiting for code review |\n   122вҶ’| `Review in progress` | Code reviewer has picked up the task |\n   123вҶ’| `Ready for QA review` | Code reviewer completed, waiting for QA |\n   124вҶ’| `QA review in progress` | QA has picked up the task |\n   125вҶ’| `Verified` | Work on task is completed |\n   126вҶ’| `Blocked` | Task is blocked by dependencies or external factors |\n   127вҶ’\n   128вҶ’### Priority Levels\n   129вҶ’\n   130вҶ’| Priority | Name | SLA | Description |\n   131вҶ’|----------|------|-----|-------------|\n   132вҶ’| 1 | Critical | Today | Blocking production or critical path |\n   133вҶ’| 2 | High | This week | Important feature or significant bug |\n   134вҶ’| 3 | Medium | This sprint | Regular feature or improvement |\n   135вҶ’| 4 | Low | When possible | Nice-to-have or minor improvement |\n   136вҶ’\n   137вҶ’### Timestamp\n   138вҶ’> Important: Always put date and time next to task status when setting it\n   139вҶ’\n   140вҶ’Always specify task completion time strictly in format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:mm:ss (for example, 2026-02-25 10:43:00).\n   141вҶ’Don't add extra words or explanations before the date.\n   142вҶ’\n   143вҶ’**Examples:**\n   144вҶ’- `Ready for dev` - 2026-02-11 10:43:00\n   145вҶ’- `Verified` - 2025-12-24 18:15:43\n   146вҶ’\n   147вҶ’### Status Workflow\n   148вҶ’\n   149вҶ’```mermaid\n   150вҶ’flowchart TD\n   151вҶ’\n   152вҶ’A[Ready for Dev]\n   153вҶ’B[Dev in Progress]\n   154вҶ’C[Ready for Review]\n   155вҶ’D[Review in Progress]\n   156вҶ’E[Ready for QA Review]\n   157вҶ’F[QA Review in Progress]\n   158вҶ’G[Verified]\n   159вҶ’H[Blocked]\n   160вҶ’\n   161вҶ’A --> B\n   162вҶ’B --> C\n   163вҶ’C --> D\n   164вҶ’D --> E\n   165вҶ’E --> F\n   166вҶ’F --> G\n   167вҶ’\n   168вҶ’%% Rework loops\n   169вҶ’C -- changes requested --> A\n   170вҶ’F -- bugs found --> A\n   171вҶ’\n   172вҶ’%% Blocked state\n   173вҶ’A -- has unmet dependencies --> H\n   174вҶ’B -- external blocker --> H\n   175вҶ’H -- dependencies resolved --> A\n   176вҶ’H -- blocker removed --> B\n   177вҶ’```\n   178вҶ’\n   179вҶ’### Blocked Status\n   180вҶ’\n   181вҶ’Task enters `Blocked` status when:\n   182вҶ’1. `depends_on` contains a task ID that is not `Verified`\n   183вҶ’2. External blocker exists (no API access, waiting for response, etc.)\n   184вҶ’\n   185вҶ’Task exits `Blocked` status when:\n   186вҶ’1. All tasks in `depends_on` are `Verified`\n   187вҶ’2. External blocker is removed manually via `/unblock_task`\n   188вҶ’\n   189вҶ’---\n   190вҶ’\n   191вҶ’## Dependencies\n   192вҶ’\n   193вҶ’### depends_on\n   194вҶ’\n   195вҶ’Specifies tasks that must complete before this task can start.\n   196вҶ’\n   197вҶ’```yaml\n   198вҶ’depends_on:\n   199вҶ’  - \"CORE-001\"\n   200вҶ’  - \"CORE-002\"\n   201вҶ’```\n   202вҶ’\n   203вҶ’**Rules:**\n   204вҶ’- Task cannot transition from `Ready for dev` to `Dev in progress` if any dependency is not `Verified`\n   205вҶ’- If dependencies are not met, task goes to `Blocked` status\n   206вҶ’- Circular dependencies are not allowed\n   207вҶ’\n   208вҶ’### blocks\n   209вҶ’\n   210вҶ’Specifies tasks that are waiting for this task to complete.\n   211вҶ’\n   212вҶ’```yaml\n   213вҶ’blocks:\n   214вҶ’  - \"CORE-005\"\n   215вҶ’  - \"CORE-006\"\n   216вҶ’```\n   217вҶ’\n   218вҶ’**Rules:**\n   219вҶ’- Automatically populated when another task has this task in its `depends_on`\n   22