          "text": "     1вҶ’# Task Performer Plugin\n     2вҶ’\n     3вҶ’Structured development workflow plugin for Claude Code with automated code review and QA verification for mobile applications.\n     4вҶ’\n     5вҶ’## Overview\n     6вҶ’\n     7вҶ’Task Performer is a Claude Code plugin that orchestrates a complete development workflow for Android projects. It provides specialized agents and skills to handle:\n     8вҶ’\n     9вҶ’- **Development** - Implementation of features following best practices\n    10вҶ’- **Code Review** - Comprehensive code analysis with actionable feedback\n    11вҶ’- **QA Verification** - Build, tests, coverage, security, and accessibility checks\n    12вҶ’\n    13вҶ’## Installation\n    14вҶ’\n    15вҶ’In Claude Code, register the marketplace first:\n    16вҶ’`/plugin marketplace add memksim/workflow-marketplace`\n    17вҶ’\n    18вҶ’Then install the plugin from this marketplace:\n    19вҶ’`/plugin install task-performer@workflow-plugins`\n    20вҶ’\n    21вҶ’### Directory Structure\n    22вҶ’\n    23вҶ’After installation, your project should have:\n    24вҶ’\n    25вҶ’```\n    26вҶ’your-project/\n    27вҶ’в””в”Җв”Җ .claude/\n    28вҶ’    в””в”Җв”Җ tasks/\n    29вҶ’        в””в”Җв”Җ <TASK-ID>/\n    30вҶ’            в”ңв”Җв”Җ task.md\n    31вҶ’            в”ңв”Җв”Җ dev_result.md\n    32вҶ’            в”ңв”Җв”Җ review_result.md\n    33вҶ’            в””в”Җв”Җ qa_review_result.md\n    34вҶ’```\n    35вҶ’\n    36вҶ’## Agents\n    37вҶ’\n    38вҶ’### senior-android-developer\n    39вҶ’\n    40вҶ’Senior Android developer agent for:\n    41вҶ’- Architecture decisions (MVI, MVVM, Clean Architecture)\n    42вҶ’- Kotlin/Java implementation\n    43вҶ’- Jetpack Compose UI development\n    44вҶ’- Performance optimization\n    45вҶ’- Testing strategies\n    46вҶ’\n    47вҶ’### android-code-reviewer\n    48вҶ’\n    49вҶ’Code review specialist that analyzes:\n    50вҶ’- Architecture compliance\n    51вҶ’- Code style and conventions\n    52вҶ’- Bug detection (NPE, memory leaks, race conditions)\n    53вҶ’- Security vulnerabilities\n    54вҶ’\n    55вҶ’### qa-expert\n    56вҶ’\n    57вҶ’Quality assurance agent that verifies:\n    58вҶ’- Build status (debug/release)\n    59вҶ’- Autotest execution and results\n    60вҶ’- Test coverage analysis\n    61вҶ’- Security audit (OWASP Mobile Top 10)\n    62вҶ’- Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1 AA)\n    63вҶ’\n    64вҶ’## Skills\n    65вҶ’\n    66вҶ’### task_management\n    67вҶ’\n    68вҶ’Manages task lifecycle and status transitions:\n    69вҶ’\n    70вҶ’```\n    71вҶ’Ready for dev вҶ’ Dev in progress вҶ’ Ready for review вҶ’ Review in progress вҶ’ Ready for QA Review вҶ’ QA Review in progress вҶ’ Verified\n    72вҶ’```\n    73вҶ’\n    74вҶ’### developer_result\n    75вҶ’\n    76вҶ’Records development work results including:\n    77вҶ’- What was done\n    78вҶ’- Where changes were made\n    79вҶ’- How to verify\n    80вҶ’- Tests added\n    81вҶ’- Risks and limitations\n    82вҶ’\n    83вҶ’### code_review_result\n    84вҶ’\n    85вҶ’Records code review findings:\n    86вҶ’- Architecture assessment\n    87вҶ’- Potential bugs\n    88вҶ’- Performance issues\n    89вҶ’- Security concerns\n    90вҶ’- Severity classification\n    91вҶ’\n    92вҶ’### qa_review_result\n    93вҶ’\n    94вҶ’Records QA verification results:\n    95вҶ’- Build status\n    96вҶ’- Test results and coverage\n    97вҶ’- Security audit findings\n    98вҶ’- Accessibility compliance\n    99вҶ’- Quality score\n   100вҶ’\n   101вҶ’## Workflow\n   102вҶ’\n   103вҶ’### 1. Create a Task\n   104вҶ’\n   105вҶ’Create a task file at `.claude/tasks/<TASK-ID>/task.md`:\n   106вҶ’\n   107вҶ’```markdown\n   108вҶ’# MUSIC-009\n   109вҶ’\n   110вҶ’## Title\n   111вҶ’Add progress indicator around track cover\n   112вҶ’\n   113вҶ’## Problem\n   114вҶ’User doesn't understand how much time remains until end of track.\n   115вҶ’\n   116вҶ’## Task\n   117вҶ’Implement circular progress bar around album cover.\n   118вҶ’Progress should update every second.\n   119вҶ’\n   120вҶ’## Constraints\n   121вҶ’- Use Jetpack Compose\n   122вҶ’- No third-party libraries\n   123вҶ’- Don't degrade performance\n   124вҶ’\n   125вҶ’## Team\n   126вҶ’- senior-android-developer\n   127вҶ’- android-code-reviewer\n   128вҶ’- qa-expert\n   129вҶ’\n   130вҶ’## Status\n   131вҶ’Ready for dev - 2026-01-12 12:15:12\n   132вҶ’```\n   133вҶ’\n   134вҶ’### 2. Run Development\n   135вҶ’\n   136вҶ’Ask Claude to work on the task:\n   137вҶ’```\n   138вҶ’Work on task MUSIC-009\n   139вҶ’```\n   140вҶ’\n   141вҶ’The plugin will:\n   142вҶ’1. Assign the task to `senior-android-developer`\n   143вҶ’2. Implement the feature\n   144вҶ’3. Run code review via `android-code-reviewer`\n   145вҶ’4. Run QA verification via `qa-expert`\n   146вҶ’5. Update task status through the workflow\n   147вҶ’\n   148вҶ’### 3. Track Progress\n   149вҶ’\n   150вҶ’Task status transitions:\n   151вҶ’- `Ready for dev` - Waiting for developer\n   152вҶ’- `Dev in progress` - Developer working\n   153вҶ’- `Ready for review` - Development complete, waiting for review\n   154вҶ’- `Review in progress` - Code review in progress\n   155вҶ’- `Ready for QA Review` - Review complete, waiting for QA\n   156вҶ’- `QA Review in progress` - QA verification in progress\n   157вҶ’- `Verified` - All checks passed\n   158вҶ’\n   159вҶ’## Task Files\n   160вҶ’\n   161вҶ’Each task generates several files:\n   162вҶ’\n   163вҶ’| File | Purpose |\n   164вҶ’|------|---------|\n   165вҶ’| `task.md` | Task description and status |\n   166вҶ’| `dev_result.md` | Development results |\n   167вҶ’| `review_result.md` | Code review findings |\n   168вҶ’| `qa_review_result.md` | QA verification results |\n   169вҶ’\n   170вҶ’## Examples\n   171вҶ’\n   172вҶ’Example files are available in the `skills/*/examples/` directories.\n   173вҶ’\n   174вҶ’## License\n   175вҶ’\n   176вҶ’MIT License - see [LICENSE](LICENSE) for details.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you sho