etection (NPE, memory leaks, race conditions)\n    53вҶ’- Security vulnerabilities\n    54вҶ’\n    55вҶ’### qa-expert\n    56вҶ’\n    57вҶ’Quality assurance agent that verifies:\n    58вҶ’- Build status (debug/release)\n    59вҶ’- Autotest execution and results\n    60вҶ’- Test coverage analysis\n    61вҶ’- Security audit (OWASP Mobile Top 10)\n    62вҶ’- Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1 AA)\n    63вҶ’\n    64вҶ’## Skills\n    65вҶ’\n    66вҶ’\n    67вҶ’\n    68вҶ’## Workflow\n    69вҶ’\n    70вҶ’### User workflow\n    71вҶ’1. `/make_task ABC-123`\n    72вҶ’2. `/perform_task ABC-123`\n    73вҶ’\n    74вҶ’### Agents workflow\n    75вҶ’```mermaid\n    76вҶ’```mermaid\n    77вҶ’flowchart TD\n    78вҶ’\n    79вҶ’A[Ready for Dev]\n    80вҶ’A --> B[Dev in Progress]\n    81вҶ’B --> C[Ready for Review]\n    82вҶ’C --> D[Review in Progress]\n    83вҶ’D --> E[Ready for QA Review]\n    84вҶ’E --> F[QA Review in Progress]\n    85вҶ’F --> G[Verified]\n    86вҶ’\n    87вҶ’%% Rework loops\n    88вҶ’C -- changes requested --> A\n    89вҶ’F -- bugs found --> A\n    90вҶ’```\n    91вҶ’\n    92вҶ’## Task Files\n    93вҶ’\n    94вҶ’Each task generates several files:\n    95вҶ’\n    96вҶ’| File | Purpose |\n    97вҶ’|------|---------|\n    98вҶ’| `task.md` | Task description and status |\n    99вҶ’| `dev_result.md` | Development results |\n   100вҶ’| `review_result.md` | Code review findings |\n   101вҶ’| `qa_review_result.md` | QA verification results |\n   102вҶ’\n   103вҶ’## Examples\n   104вҶ’\n   105вҶ’Example files are available in the `skills/*/examples/` directories.\n   106вҶ’\n   107вҶ’## License\n   108вҶ’\n   109вҶ’MIT License - see [LICENSE](LICENSE) for details.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n",
